Source: linux-management-system
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Linux Management System <admin@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), python3, python3-venv, python3-pip
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/Kensan196948G/Linux-Management-System
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: linux-management-system
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), python3-venv, python3-pip, nginx, adduser
Recommends: curl, ca-certificates, git
Description: Webmin-compatible Linux Server Management WebUI
 Security-first Linux server management system with JWT authentication,
 RBAC (Role-Based Access Control), sudo allowlist, and audit logging.
 .
 Features:
  - System status monitoring and service management
  - User and group management via approval workflow
  - Log viewer with real-time streaming
  - Network configuration and firewall management
  - Hardware monitoring (CPU, memory, disk, SMART)
  - Cron job management
  - Package management with diff preview
  - Audit trail for all operations
 .
 Security model:
  - All privileged operations via sudo wrapper scripts (allowlist only)
  - JWT-based authentication with configurable expiry
  - Input validation with forbidden character detection
  - Full audit logging of all operations
